WEBVTT

00:00.358 --> 00:01.568
<i>So here's what's you missed
<i>Kurt pulled</i></i>

00:01.569 --> 00:03.779
<i>a last-minute switcheroo
for Carmen Tibideaux</i>

00:03.780 --> 00:05.665
<i>and nailed his NYADA audition,
while Rachel</i>

00:05.666 --> 00:07.216
<i>tried her old "Don't Rain
on My Parade" standby</i>

00:07.217 --> 00:08.117
<i>which we've all heard now,
like, a bajillion times,</i>

00:08.202 --> 00:09.669
<i>and she totally choked.</i>

00:09.736 --> 00:11.370
<i>Bieste admitted that
her husband Cooter hit her,</i>

00:11.371 --> 00:13.764
<i>but she lied and said she left
him, when actually, she stayed.</i>

00:13.840 --> 00:16.075
<i>Puck isn't graduating, which he
pretends not to care about...</i>

00:16.076 --> 00:17.434
I'm too stupid. <i>but a while
back, he told everybody</i>

00:17.511 --> 00:18.744
<i>that graduating high school
was something</i>

00:18.745 --> 00:20.246
<i>he was really
looking forward to.</i>

00:20.247 --> 00:22.265
<i>The Glee Club's been ignoring
Tina all year long.</i>

00:22.349 --> 00:23.916
Tina won't mind being recast.
No, she won't.

00:23.917 --> 00:25.817
<i>Actually, she kind of got
ignored last year, too.</i>

00:25.852 --> 00:27.053
<i>Actually, Tina's sort of been
ignored the whole time</i>

00:27.054 --> 00:28.304
<i>and she's been
in the New Directions!</i>

00:28.305 --> 00:30.389
<i>since, like forever.</i>

00:30.390 --> 00:31.924
<i>The first time she got a solo,
she insisted she was bad</i>

00:31.925 --> 00:33.425
<i>and forced Mr. Shue
to give the song to Rachel,</i>

00:33.426 --> 00:34.810
<i>and ever solo since, she's
either gotten booed</i>

00:34.811 --> 00:36.312
<i>or started crying
uncontrollably.</i>

00:36.313 --> 00:37.863
<i>No one noticed that she went
from dressing punk</i>

00:37.864 --> 00:39.315
<i>to dressing Goth to dressing
like a go-go dancer</i>

00:39.316 --> 00:40.582
<i>in '60s Swinging London.</i>

00:40.617 --> 00:41.541
<i>She even got Mike Chang
into college,</i>

00:41.568 --> 00:43.069
<i>and she hardly got a thank you.</i>

00:43.070 --> 00:44.287
<i>Sometimes people don't even
seem to know her name.</i>

00:44.288 --> 00:45.705
Girl Chang...
Tina Blowin' Wang...

00:45.706 --> 00:47.206
Asian Horror Movie!

00:47.207 --> 00:49.207
<i>And that's what
you missed on</i> Glee.

00:50.894 --> 00:54.546
Porcelain, Weezy,
you created a monster.

00:56.767 --> 01:00.268
They're calling Jessie
St. James a visionary,

01:00.320 --> 01:02.221
and lauding Vocal Adrenaline

01:02.222 --> 01:04.322
for their ongoing
commitment to diversity.

01:04.391 --> 01:06.659
But Jessie St. James was against
Unique performing

01:06.660 --> 01:08.077
as his true magical self.

01:08.078 --> 01:10.246
No, we were the ones who
convinced him to do that.

01:10.247 --> 01:11.446
Well, then, you only have
yourselves to blame.

01:11.448 --> 01:13.616
And the liberal media.

01:13.700 --> 01:14.866
Not really.
It was your idea.

01:14.901 --> 01:15.993
I have no memory of that.

01:16.036 --> 01:17.536
In any case, Unique is now

01:17.537 --> 01:19.922
a show choir celebrity.

01:20.006 --> 01:22.124
He/She will trounce us
at Nationals,

01:22.125 --> 01:24.418
and I will lose my Cheerios!
to Coach Roz Washington.

01:24.428 --> 01:26.178
I will not let that happen.

01:26.179 --> 01:28.914
We have but
one choice left to us:

01:28.915 --> 01:31.425
It's time to fight fire

01:31.468 --> 01:36.255
with the flaming flames
of additional flamey gay fire.

01:38.692 --> 01:40.976
Porcelain, you will
wear this flapper dress

01:40.977 --> 01:43.446
and perform at Nationals
as Porcelina.

01:43.530 --> 01:45.764
You already have the lady
gait and the lady voice,

01:45.816 --> 01:48.234
and you'll have to start
smoking, though,

01:48.235 --> 01:49.435
because this dress
is a size two.

01:49.486 --> 01:50.569
Okay, just because I'm gay
does not mean

01:50.570 --> 01:52.070
I like to dress up like a woman.

01:52.072 --> 01:53.038
Oh, come on.

01:53.039 --> 01:54.440
What about Halloween, Kurt?

01:55.709 --> 01:58.035
Trick or treat!
Ba-da bing!

01:58.044 --> 01:59.611
Ay, what's a guy gotta do

01:59.612 --> 02:02.248
to get a candy situation
up in here, huh?

02:02.299 --> 02:04.333
Okay, that was a
Halloween costume,

02:04.334 --> 02:07.002
and it is a far cry from starting out
on the stage at Nationals in a dress.

02:07.053 --> 02:08.794
Which is absolutely
out of the question.

02:08.839 --> 02:10.589
Well, then, the
New Directions! will lose.

02:10.590 --> 02:12.391
Hate to say it, kiddo,

02:12.459 --> 02:15.845
but if we want to beat Vocal
Adrenaline at Nationals,

02:15.846 --> 02:17.262
it's tuckin' time.

