05:10.904 --> 05:12.938
You've reaed the
office of Carmen Tibideaux,

05:12.939 --> 05:14.573
Dean of Vocal Performance,
at the New York Academy

05:14.574 --> 05:15.658
of Dramatic Arts.

05:15.659 --> 05:17.493
Please leave a message
after the tone.

05:18.995 --> 05:21.380
Hi, Madame Tibideaux, this is
Rachel Berry calling.

05:21.448 --> 05:24.450
I understand that
14 messages is a lot,

05:24.451 --> 05:25.868
but I just wanted to make sure

05:25.869 --> 05:27.503
that you got the muffin basket
that I sent

05:27.504 --> 05:30.506
as well as the invitation to
come and see my show choir

05:30.507 --> 05:32.207
perform at our Nationals
in Chicago.

05:32.208 --> 05:36.128
Every year, the judges give out
an award for an MVP,

05:36.129 --> 05:37.346
and I would really love it

05:37.347 --> 05:38.681
if you could be there
to watch me win.

05:38.682 --> 05:41.266
If anything, just to show you

05:41.267 --> 05:43.018
that what happened at
my audition was a fluke

05:43.019 --> 05:45.504
and that I do have the talent
and the ability

05:45.505 --> 05:47.172
to study with you
next year at NYADA.

05:47.173 --> 05:50.693
I... I understand that asking
you to make the trip is a lot,

05:50.694 --> 05:52.394
but I'm just...
I'm really not ready

05:52.395 --> 05:54.146
to give up on my dream, so...

05:54.147 --> 05:56.649
Thank you very much.

06:04.324 --> 06:05.991
Nationals.

06:08.378 --> 06:09.628
Okay, song selection:

06:09.696 --> 06:11.863
We'll be kicking off our
"Vintage" theme

06:11.864 --> 06:13.048
with the legendary
Jim Steinman's

06:13.133 --> 06:15.084
"Paradise by
the Dashboard Light."

06:15.168 --> 06:16.459
Rachel will do the solo,
"It's All Com..."

06:16.503 --> 06:18.203
"...Coming Back to Me Now."

06:18.204 --> 06:19.212
One of Celine Dion's most
powerful ballads,

06:19.222 --> 06:20.889
inspired by <i>Wuthering Heights.</i>

06:20.974 --> 06:22.558
And we'll be working in
a new Treble Tones number,

06:22.559 --> 06:24.876
utilizing the talents of our
featured performer,

06:24.877 --> 06:26.261
Porcelina Hummel.

06:26.346 --> 06:27.813
Not gonna happen,
Dragon Lady.

06:27.880 --> 06:29.055
Oh, you'll do
as you're told, he/she.

06:29.065 --> 06:30.599
We will be performing

06:30.600 --> 06:32.401
"What A Feeling,"
from <i>Flashdance,</i>

06:32.402 --> 06:34.570
and I'm familiar with the
choreography, of course,

06:34.571 --> 06:36.187
because I was Jennifer Beals'
dance double.

06:36.206 --> 06:37.355
And on that note,

06:37.390 --> 06:38.607
please look under your seats.

06:43.329 --> 06:44.580
Space helmets.

06:44.581 --> 06:46.915
Welding helmets
and leg warmers?!

06:47.000 --> 06:49.451
Best way to get props
is to use props.

06:49.502 --> 06:50.753
I am your father.

06:50.754 --> 06:52.120
Uh, Darth Vader.

06:52.122 --> 06:53.204
Is that a movie?

06:53.239 --> 06:54.790
A healthy dose of props,

06:54.874 --> 06:57.000
and our plucky transsexual
Porcelina,

06:57.043 --> 06:58.126
and you are over the top.

06:58.178 --> 07:00.412
Aren't props a little cheesy?

07:00.413 --> 07:03.132
Guys, I've asked for Sue's
help because she's a winner,

07:03.216 --> 07:05.634
and I'm not ashamed to admit
this... I want to win.

07:05.719 --> 07:07.686
But there's not one
person in that audience

07:07.687 --> 07:09.555
who will think we're
anything but underdogs

07:09.606 --> 07:11.106
who would be lucky to
place in Nationals.

07:11.191 --> 07:12.758
We didn't even make
the top ten last year.

07:12.759 --> 07:16.862
We've got one last week to come
together and shake things up.

07:16.929 --> 07:19.264
If there's anyone here
who is not up for trying

07:19.265 --> 07:20.699
and working their butts off,

07:20.700 --> 07:21.867
you should just get up
right now and leave.

07:23.620 --> 07:25.154
Whoa, whoa, Tina,
where you going?

07:25.238 --> 07:26.872
You guys don't need me...
carry on.

07:26.939 --> 07:28.448
Tina, you don't understand.
I need this.

07:28.458 --> 07:29.775
Because you blew an audition?

07:29.776 --> 07:31.326
That's not a reason for you

07:31.377 --> 07:32.611
to get a solo at Nationals.

07:32.662 --> 07:33.879
Maybe the rest of us
would like one, too.

07:33.946 --> 07:35.538
I wouldn't mind
another one

07:35.582 --> 07:36.799
before I get deported.

07:36.800 --> 07:38.500
I want one.
Even though I can't sing.

07:38.551 --> 07:39.751
Tina, Rachel is a senior.

07:39.786 --> 07:40.753
So are you, but you can bet

07:40.754 --> 07:41.720
the only thing you'll be doing

07:41.721 --> 07:42.879
is a dance break with Brittany.

07:42.922 --> 07:44.289
Other people matter.

07:44.340 --> 07:45.891
Tina, you may not always
get all the solos,

07:45.892 --> 07:46.966
but you are a key player.

07:47.010 --> 07:48.510
I put you in charge
of costumes.

07:48.561 --> 07:50.295
Wow! Like that's some prize.

07:50.363 --> 07:51.563
You want props
to move around?

07:51.631 --> 07:53.999
Well, I'm a human prop,
and I'm sick of it!

07:54.067 --> 07:55.725
Take a lap and cool down,
Asian Number One.

07:55.769 --> 07:57.770
My name is Tina.

07:57.771 --> 07:59.137
Tina Cohen Chang!

08:04.277 --> 08:05.577
Isn't she the one
who used to stutter?

08:05.578 --> 08:07.312
You're being selfish.

08:07.313 --> 08:08.313
How come when Rachel complains

08:08.314 --> 08:09.314
about not getting enough solos,

08:09.315 --> 08:10.365
she's "claiming her stardom,"

08:10.366 --> 08:11.324
but when I do it,
it's selfish.

08:11.334 --> 08:12.501
You're a junior.

08:12.502 --> 08:13.702
You'll get your
change next year.

08:13.703 --> 08:15.487
This is the seniors'
moment to shine.

08:15.538 --> 08:19.007
I'm really
disappointed in you.

08:19.008 --> 08:21.827
Tina, look, I understand
that you feel like

08:21.878 --> 08:23.595
your voice is being stifled
right now, in the Glee Club.

08:23.663 --> 08:24.963
I mean, I have no idea
why you would choose

08:24.964 --> 08:26.548
this moment specifically
to make a stink about it

08:26.633 --> 08:29.000
but I want you to know
that you are being heard.

08:29.001 --> 08:31.386
Which is why I'm willing
to offer you $50

08:31.471 --> 08:32.855
just to let this all go
until after Nationals.

08:34.440 --> 08:36.441
Do you have any idea how
important Nationals is to me?

08:36.442 --> 08:37.893
I mean, if I can convince
Carmen Tibideaux

08:37.894 --> 08:39.311
to come and
watch us perform,

08:39.312 --> 08:41.513
then it's basically like
a do-over for my NYADA audition,

08:41.514 --> 08:44.349
which means that my entire future
depends on us being amazing,

08:44.350 --> 08:46.034
which means that everyone
needs to do their part.

08:46.119 --> 08:47.861
Their part
to make you look good.

08:47.904 --> 08:51.990
I have sat, for three years,
in the back of that choir room,

08:52.041 --> 08:54.409
holding Mike's hand or
crying or smiling and swaying,

08:54.494 --> 08:57.296
while everyone else was
out there singing solos.

08:57.363 --> 08:59.832
Maybe I say something,
most of the time I don't,

08:59.833 --> 09:01.216
team player all the way.

09:01.217 --> 09:03.919
I am tired of being silent.

09:04.003 --> 09:05.838
I am one of the original
Glee Club members,

09:05.889 --> 09:07.840
and I was singing "Sit Down
You're Rockin' the Boat"

09:07.891 --> 09:09.308
when Finn and Puck were
still throwing Slushees at us.

09:09.309 --> 09:10.726
So when is it my turn?

09:10.810 --> 09:13.846
Do you have any idea how
difficult it is to be me?

09:13.847 --> 09:16.515
Do you have a Facebook
account or Twitter account?

09:16.516 --> 09:17.932
Yes. Do you have
time to watch Bravo

09:17.934 --> 09:20.068
or read a book or buy laces

09:20.069 --> 09:21.144
for your incredibly
high comical boots.

09:21.187 --> 09:23.105
Okay? I don't.

09:23.106 --> 09:24.656
It's exhausting being me.

09:24.657 --> 09:26.057
I get up at 5:00
in the morning

09:26.058 --> 09:27.192
just to get all
of this prepared,

09:27.193 --> 09:28.443
in case a solo
is thrown my way.

09:28.528 --> 09:31.280
I have the entire Sondheim,
Hamlisch, Lloyd-Webber,

09:31.364 --> 09:32.664
Elton John songbooks
memorized,

09:32.732 --> 09:34.232
including every single
Katy Perry hit, as well.

09:34.233 --> 09:37.035
And I do all of this while
keeping my boyfriend interested

09:37.069 --> 09:38.170
and physically satisfied

09:38.171 --> 09:39.755
and being the captain
of 16 clubs

09:39.756 --> 09:41.573
and keeping a 3.86 GPA.

09:41.624 --> 09:43.708
I could do all of that.
And you will.

09:43.743 --> 09:45.093
Next year.

09:45.094 --> 09:47.579
You'll have your
chance next year.

09:47.630 --> 09:51.183
All I want is, for one moment,
to feel like you...

09:51.184 --> 09:53.886
be up on that stage and get one
of the standing ovations

09:53.887 --> 09:55.137
you're so used to getting.

10:03.529 --> 10:05.197
I mean, I'm behind you 100%.

10:05.264 --> 10:06.865
Being gay doesn't mean
you're a cross-dresser.

10:06.866 --> 10:08.317
I mean, that's just silly.

10:08.401 --> 10:10.769
Oh, you did not just text me
that, Michael Robert Chang.

10:10.820 --> 10:12.537
Is that Tina?

10:12.538 --> 10:13.872
Hey, Tina.
What are you doing here?

10:13.940 --> 10:16.124
Fulfilling my duties
as costume coordinator

10:16.125 --> 10:17.376
and text-fighting with Mike,
who says

10:17.377 --> 10:18.577
my outburst in
Glee Club was unreasonable.

10:18.578 --> 10:19.577
Well, we're getting a hot
pretzel later,

10:19.579 --> 10:21.129
if you want to join us.

10:21.214 --> 10:22.714
Can't.
Have to go find gown fabric

10:22.715 --> 10:24.115
that doesn't clash with
the high yellow undertones

10:24.116 --> 10:25.500
of Rachel Berry's complexion.

10:25.501 --> 10:26.668
Oh...

10:30.173 --> 10:32.758
I can do everything
Rachel Berry can.

10:35.962 --> 10:37.679
Oh, my God!
Tina! Tina!

10:37.680 --> 10:39.297
Tina! Oh, my God! Oh, oh, oh!
Get her, get her, get her!

10:39.298 --> 10:40.298
Tina, are you okay?

10:40.299 --> 10:41.600
Can you hear me?
Look at me.

10:41.601 --> 10:43.643
Oh, my God, this is
like <i>Days of our Lives.</i>

10:43.653 --> 10:44.769
Can you hear me?

10:44.771 --> 10:46.021
Lost...
It's me...

10:46.105 --> 10:47.105
Kurt.
Rachel, it's me.

10:47.156 --> 10:48.690
Did you just
call me Rachel?

10:50.076 --> 10:51.660
Rachel, Kurt and I just saw you

10:51.661 --> 10:52.861
fall into the fountain.

10:52.862 --> 10:54.079
We think you may have
hit your head.

10:54.146 --> 10:55.530
We need to get you back
to the Glee Club, ASAP.

10:55.581 --> 10:57.666
Why?

10:57.667 --> 10:58.984
And we need to get
your solo ready,

10:58.985 --> 11:00.202
so you can win us
a national championship.

11:05.591 --> 11:08.794
Oh, my God...
I'm Rachel Berry.

11:10.886 --> 11:12.203
Rachel, I know you're
under a lot of pressure,

11:12.204 --> 11:13.304
but I need you
to come with me

11:13.305 --> 11:14.389
to Between the Sheets
after school.

11:14.390 --> 11:15.540
I'm in desperate need
of sheet music,

11:15.541 --> 11:16.808
and you're the only one
who can help me.

11:16.809 --> 11:18.009
If you want to run into your

11:18.010 --> 11:19.210
old pal Chandler,
far be it from me

11:19.211 --> 11:20.395
to stand in your way.

11:20.396 --> 11:21.513
We've been through this
a million times.

11:21.514 --> 11:22.647
It was just
a few text messages...

11:22.648 --> 11:23.815
Oh, hey there, Hobbit.

11:23.816 --> 11:24.899
Can't wait to
hear your solo

11:24.900 --> 11:26.401
in Glee Club today.

11:26.402 --> 11:28.603
Hope you don't choke like
you did in your NYADA audition.

11:28.604 --> 11:31.773
Rachel, I don't want to put
any more pressure on you,

11:31.774 --> 11:33.408
but winning at Nationals will
be the most important thing

11:33.409 --> 11:35.076
that will ever happen to me
in my entire life.

11:35.077 --> 11:36.494
I mean, you'll
basically be performing

11:36.495 --> 11:38.563
for every handi-capable kid
in the entire world.

11:38.564 --> 11:40.832
Mercedes?
Mmm, praise.

