16:13.472 --> 16:15.506
Hey, Tina, can I talk to you?

16:15.507 --> 16:16.808
I wanted to say
you're always

16:16.809 --> 16:18.342
so good in my musical numbers.

16:18.343 --> 16:20.352
Your oohs and aahs
are always on pitch,

16:20.412 --> 16:22.680
and your light sashaying makes
my tour de force performances

16:22.681 --> 16:24.398
even more spine-tingling,
if that's even possible.

16:24.399 --> 16:26.234
I appreciate it, and you.

16:26.235 --> 16:27.785
Rachel, I can't tell you
how long

16:27.786 --> 16:29.370
I've waited
to hear you say that.

16:29.371 --> 16:30.688
Just because you're

16:30.689 --> 16:32.156
a little more
in the background this year,

16:32.157 --> 16:34.125
don't doubt
your talent, Tina.

16:34.126 --> 16:35.793
Next year is all you.

16:35.794 --> 16:38.195
It's finally your chance
to shine.

16:41.216 --> 16:42.800
I couldn't believe it
when I heard that your

16:42.801 --> 16:44.836
NYADA audition
didn't go well.

16:44.837 --> 16:46.804
You're...
you're always so amazing.

16:46.805 --> 16:48.873
I wish Madame Tibideaux
agreed with you.

16:48.874 --> 16:51.542
So change her mind. I've tried.
She won't even return my calls.

16:51.543 --> 16:53.144
That's not the Rachel Berry
I know.

16:53.145 --> 16:54.929
If I were you,
I'd drive

16:54.930 --> 16:57.265
to wherever she is and I'd stay

16:57.266 --> 17:00.268
until I convinced Ms. Tibideaux
to give me another shot.

17:00.269 --> 17:01.769
I can't believe
how supportive you are

17:01.770 --> 17:03.721
when half the time,
I can't even be bothered

17:03.722 --> 17:05.690
to thank you for your tremendous
supporting performances.

17:05.691 --> 17:07.391
It's not completely selfless.

17:07.392 --> 17:09.076
You're our secret weapon,
Rachel Berry,

17:09.077 --> 17:11.112
and by helping you,
I help us all.

17:14.700 --> 17:16.917
Oh, my God, Tina! Are you okay?
Get her! Get her! Get her!

17:16.919 --> 17:19.753
Tina. Oh, my God, are you okay?
Ooh! Ooh, ooh!

17:19.755 --> 17:21.172
Ugh.

17:21.173 --> 17:23.708
Did she have to take in the
bolt of fabric with her?

17:23.709 --> 17:26.377
That silk charmeuse is worth,
like, 25 bucks a yard.

17:32.568 --> 17:34.219
A-five, six, seven, eight.

17:34.220 --> 17:36.288
Mask, mask, helmet down.

17:36.289 --> 17:38.406
Pivot, pivot.

17:38.407 --> 17:40.242
Jump, mask, boys.

17:40.243 --> 17:43.060
A-one, two, three,
four, five, six.

17:43.079 --> 17:45.213
Burn! Burn!

17:45.214 --> 17:46.581
Burn! Come on!

17:46.582 --> 17:47.716
Let it burn!

17:47.717 --> 17:49.084
Set this joint on fire!

17:49.085 --> 17:52.304
Come on, burn the joint down!

17:52.305 --> 17:54.055
Okay, cut the music.
Stop! Stop.

17:54.056 --> 17:57.175
This is an unmitigated disaster.

17:57.176 --> 17:59.628
Jennifer Beals
is spinning in her grave.

17:59.629 --> 18:04.065
Gentlemen, I asked for a cascade
of sparks timed to the rhythm.

18:04.066 --> 18:06.968
- I can't see through this helmet.
- I took mine off.

18:06.969 --> 18:09.037
Metal sparks in your face is how you get freckles.
Is this even legal?

18:09.038 --> 18:10.355
Yeah,
shouldn't we be in

18:10.356 --> 18:11.639
some sort of grinding union?
Wanky.

18:11.640 --> 18:12.774
Sue, they're right.

18:12.775 --> 18:14.576
They can't pick up
advanced choreography

18:14.577 --> 18:16.661
when they're weighed down
by helmets and metal grinders.

18:16.662 --> 18:18.947
Grind, grind, pivot, kick,
pivot, spin, flip, split.

18:18.948 --> 18:20.499
What's complicated
about that?

18:20.500 --> 18:22.200
These props were supposed
to add to the routine,

18:22.201 --> 18:23.502
not be the routine.

18:23.503 --> 18:25.337
Well, maybe
you're right, William.

18:25.338 --> 18:27.506
Maybe basic
sheet metal work

18:27.507 --> 18:30.509
is just too much for
your 12th place choir.

18:30.510 --> 18:32.827
Porcelain, thoughts?

18:32.828 --> 18:35.046
I'm not doing a drag number.

18:35.047 --> 18:36.598
We need a new approach.

18:36.599 --> 18:38.266
I have an idea.

18:39.936 --> 18:41.853
This is the
teachers' lounge.

18:41.854 --> 18:43.555
It is our sacred space.

18:43.556 --> 18:45.190
Britt and I are gay
and Mercedes is black,

18:45.191 --> 18:47.058
so kicking us out
would be a hate crime.

18:47.059 --> 18:48.343
Well, I'm not totally
gay, but I think

18:48.344 --> 18:49.811
that trees are born the
same way as babies,

18:49.812 --> 18:50.979
so kicking me out

18:50.980 --> 18:52.113
would be
kind of mean.

18:52.114 --> 18:53.448
Yeah. Thanks.

18:54.617 --> 18:56.034
I'm eating my chicken, ladies.

18:56.035 --> 18:57.685
You're still wearing
your wedding ring.

18:57.686 --> 18:58.954
And I saw you

18:58.955 --> 19:00.789
last night
at the 7:00 p.m. showing

19:00.790 --> 19:02.857
of <i>21 Jump Street...</i>
with Cooter.

19:02.858 --> 19:04.626
Cooter was in <i>21 Jump Street?</i>

19:04.627 --> 19:06.294
I didn't know
he was an actor.

19:06.295 --> 19:07.462
You told us
you were leaving him.

19:07.463 --> 19:08.630
You lied to us.

19:08.631 --> 19:10.248
I know how this looks,

19:10.249 --> 19:12.417
but you just don't understand
how complicated

19:12.418 --> 19:14.169
adult relationships can be.

19:14.170 --> 19:15.720
I mean, he hit you
and you stayed.

19:15.721 --> 19:17.806
What's complicated
about that?

19:17.807 --> 19:20.425
I'm very sorry if this
is confusing for you,

19:20.426 --> 19:22.093
but what's the world worth

19:22.094 --> 19:23.979
if people don't get
a second chance?

19:23.980 --> 19:25.981
Wait, so you're saying
he changed?

19:25.982 --> 19:29.734
Well, he knows now that if he
treats me bad again, I am out.

19:29.735 --> 19:31.987
You're so selfish!

19:31.988 --> 19:34.356
You're selfish for
making me feel this way,

19:34.357 --> 19:36.157
and I hate feeling
like this.

19:36.158 --> 19:37.892
You know you
push my buttons!

19:44.200 --> 19:45.367
I don't know.

19:45.368 --> 19:46.734
Can people change that fast?

19:46.735 --> 19:48.286
I mean, most guys I know
don't even know how

19:48.287 --> 19:50.071
- to change their own underwear.
- I couldn't really

19:50.072 --> 19:51.957
figure that out, so I just
stopped wearing any at all.

19:51.958 --> 19:53.574
I think you need
to get out of the house,

19:53.575 --> 19:54.759
if only for a weekend.

19:54.760 --> 19:56.077
Come with us
to Nationals.

19:56.078 --> 19:57.712
You have two
chaperones already.

19:57.713 --> 19:59.464
I don't even know
if I'm welcome

19:59.465 --> 20:01.182
back in Chicago
after I body-slammed

20:01.183 --> 20:02.767
Refrigerator Perry
in a bar fight.

20:02.768 --> 20:04.302
We care about you, Coach.

20:04.303 --> 20:05.971
We just want to see you safe.

20:05.972 --> 20:10.758
Thank you, girls,
but I can take care of myself.

20:13.529 --> 20:15.480
Please ignore the
stench of mildew

20:15.481 --> 20:16.865
and jock strap

20:16.866 --> 20:19.067
and focus your attention
on the screen.

20:19.068 --> 20:19.901
Porcelina?

20:21.570 --> 20:23.989
Yesterday, I snuck into
a Vocal Adrenaline rehearsal,

20:23.990 --> 20:26.274
and what I saw
is not for the faint of heart.

20:26.275 --> 20:27.409
Lights.

20:33.332 --> 20:34.833
Why is this
in black and white?

20:34.834 --> 20:36.084
Because I worship <i>The Artist.</i>

20:36.085 --> 20:37.502
Look at that.

20:37.503 --> 20:39.804
Unlike you misfit,
ragtag stumblebums,

20:39.805 --> 20:43.224
each member of Vocal Adrenaline
is in perfect sync.

20:43.225 --> 20:45.493
Not a step out of place.

20:45.494 --> 20:47.562
Okay, watch this closely, guys.

20:47.563 --> 20:48.980
It's called the Human Centipede.

20:48.981 --> 20:50.732
It's the newest, hardest

20:50.733 --> 20:52.300
show choir dance move
ever invented.

20:52.301 --> 20:53.868
Incredible.

20:53.869 --> 20:55.803
That actually really
doesn't look that hard.

20:55.804 --> 20:57.305
And the cherry on top

20:57.306 --> 21:00.475
of the Vocal Adrenaline sundae
is their secret weapon, Unique.

21:00.476 --> 21:02.577
Look at him/her.

21:02.578 --> 21:04.746
Poised, confident.

21:04.747 --> 21:07.415
Pretty as a picture
with a booty that won't quit.

21:07.416 --> 21:08.867
It's the Unique factor

21:08.868 --> 21:10.785
that gives Vocal Adrenaline
its edge.

21:13.205 --> 21:15.256
Isn't Rachel our
Unique factor?

21:15.257 --> 21:16.657
Not even close.

21:16.658 --> 21:17.792
I'm not saying
that Mrs. Focker

21:17.793 --> 21:19.094
doesn't deserve a solo,

21:19.095 --> 21:20.712
but every show choir
in the country

21:20.713 --> 21:22.964
- has a little girl with a big nose.
- Okay, Sue.

21:22.965 --> 21:26.167
High school judges
are proven idiots.

21:26.168 --> 21:30.138
They love props, and Unique
is the ultimate prop.

21:30.139 --> 21:31.306
Do you seriously think
that we need

21:31.307 --> 21:32.891
a guy to dress in drag to win?

21:32.892 --> 21:34.743
- No.
- Yes.

21:34.744 --> 21:37.645
It's the only way.

21:44.537 --> 21:46.521
Sounded pretty good to me.

21:46.522 --> 21:48.540
I'm singing into the notes,
not through them,

21:48.541 --> 21:50.542
but I'll get it.

21:50.543 --> 21:52.627
It never stops
for you, does it?

21:52.628 --> 21:54.195
Well, I let myself
get overconfident once,

21:54.196 --> 21:56.064
and I'm not
going to let it happen again.

21:57.366 --> 21:59.634
Have you heard back
from Carmen Tibideaux yet?

21:59.635 --> 22:02.587
I just have to accept the
fact that I'm not going to.

22:02.588 --> 22:04.005
I've e-mailed her
and called her,

22:04.006 --> 22:06.141
and there's nothing left
that I can do.

22:06.142 --> 22:09.677
You could go see her.
It's what you suggested I do in

22:09.678 --> 22:11.279
the body-swapping
dream I had about us.

22:11.280 --> 22:14.065
When I fell in the fountain at
the mall and hit my head.

22:14.066 --> 22:16.267
It was like <i>Freaky Friday.</i>
I was you, and you were me,

22:16.268 --> 22:19.053
and Kurt was Finn, and he wanted
to have sex with me, as you.

22:19.054 --> 22:20.405
That's very disturbing.

22:20.406 --> 22:22.323
But then you, as Tina,
told me, as Rachel,

22:22.324 --> 22:23.858
"Go see Carmen Tibideaux in
person

22:23.859 --> 22:25.393
and not take no for an answer."

22:25.394 --> 22:26.778
Okay, I'm very confused.

22:26.779 --> 22:29.697
But the advice I gave myself in
your dream was good.

22:29.698 --> 22:32.450
I did some research.

22:32.451 --> 22:35.170
Carmen Tibideaux is teaching
a master class at Oberlin.

22:35.171 --> 22:38.072
If we go right now,
we can still catch her.

22:38.073 --> 22:39.374
I could drive.

22:39.375 --> 22:40.742
You would do that for me?

22:42.678 --> 22:44.629
Why? I mean, all that stuff
you said.

22:44.630 --> 22:45.913
I mean, you weren't wrong.

22:45.914 --> 22:48.683
Look, everyone is important,

22:48.684 --> 22:51.519
and I'm very sorry if I made you
feel like a supernumerary.

22:51.520 --> 22:52.637
I'm sorry.

22:52.638 --> 22:55.023
Everyone has their part
to play, right?

22:55.024 --> 22:57.058
Maybe this is mine.

22:59.111 --> 23:00.145
Thank you.

23:02.815 --> 23:04.232
You do know that next year,

23:04.233 --> 23:05.567
you're going to be
the lead female vocalist.

23:05.568 --> 23:09.487
And it's a lot of pressure,
but I'm not worried.

23:11.240 --> 23:12.657
Oh, no, please don't cry.

23:12.658 --> 23:14.409
You need to drive
Is your Hyundai gassed-up?

23:14.410 --> 23:16.211
Since Porcelain refuses
to be a team player

23:16.212 --> 23:17.662
and dress up like a lady,

23:17.663 --> 23:20.131
we're gonna have
to up our prop game.

23:20.132 --> 23:22.783
I've ordered 18 little people,
one for each of you.

23:22.784 --> 23:24.302
Wait. Little people?

23:24.303 --> 23:25.753
Munchkins.
I found 'em online, William.

23:25.754 --> 23:27.505
And don't worry,
I got a mix of race

23:27.506 --> 23:29.957
and ethnicities so you can keep up
with your little diversity charade.

23:29.958 --> 23:32.310
I can't dance with a little
person. I can hardly walk.

23:32.311 --> 23:33.961
There's that can don't attitude,
Quinn.

23:33.962 --> 23:37.065
Sue, I think maybe we are going
a little too far with the props.

23:37.066 --> 23:39.567
Let's just spend some time working
on choreography for "Dash Board."

23:39.568 --> 23:41.802
Sure, if you want to lose.

23:41.803 --> 23:43.354
Puck?

23:44.773 --> 23:45.573
Hello...

23:45.574 --> 23:46.441
My eyes are burning.

23:46.442 --> 23:47.609
Look at those legs.

23:47.610 --> 23:49.861
I am strangely
turned on right now.

23:49.862 --> 23:52.197
Please only address me
by my stage name... Lola.

23:52.198 --> 23:54.082
Puckerman, I respect your
commitment to winning,

23:54.083 --> 23:56.751
but without a doubt, you are the
ugliest woman I have ever seen.

23:56.752 --> 23:58.620
For a second there, I thought
you were Beiste's sister.

23:58.621 --> 23:59.787
It's not about being pretty.

23:59.788 --> 24:01.089
It's about someone in here
having the balls

24:01.090 --> 24:03.091
to do what he has to do
to put us over the top.

24:03.092 --> 24:04.759
Well, you know, if this is gonna
work, you're gonna have

24:04.760 --> 24:05.760
to shave off all of
your body hair.

24:05.761 --> 24:06.794
Enough!

24:06.795 --> 24:07.962
Sue, look, I really appreciate

24:07.963 --> 24:09.514
all the help
you've been giving us

24:09.515 --> 24:10.965
but I am done with all
this props madness.

24:10.966 --> 24:12.600
All we're doing for the
next three hours

24:12.601 --> 24:14.352
is learning choreography
for "Dash Board."

24:14.353 --> 24:16.187
Puck, go change.

24:16.188 --> 24:17.889
You cannot see
something like that.

24:17.890 --> 24:20.942
William, I'm oddly aroused by
your sudden forcefulness,

24:20.943 --> 24:23.194
and I will let you
handle this rehearsal,

24:23.195 --> 24:25.196
however, I feel it
necessary to warn you:

24:25.197 --> 24:27.615
I prepaid for
the little people.

24:29.902 --> 24:32.820
It's the darkest day in Ohio
since Ernest Byner. Boy, how the

24:32.821 --> 24:34.038
mighty have
truly fallen, huh?

24:34.039 --> 24:35.907
Take a good look
at him, boys.

24:35.908 --> 24:39.294
This empty, useless shell of a
man you see before you used

24:39.295 --> 24:41.028
to be the Noah Puckerman,

24:41.029 --> 24:42.863
the guy they named the Dumpster
out by the smoking lounge

24:42.864 --> 24:44.966
after 'cause he had dumped
more dweebs in it

24:44.967 --> 24:45.866
than any ten dudes
combined.

24:45.867 --> 24:47.252
Keep rocking that mullet, Ricky,

24:47.253 --> 24:49.554
Maybe it a few years it will
come back in style.

24:49.555 --> 24:52.473
And today he finally succumbed
to the toxic fumes of Glee Club

24:52.474 --> 24:55.226
and came to school wearing a fricking dress.
Are you looking

24:55.227 --> 24:57.812
to pick a fight? 'Cause there's
three of you and one of me,

24:57.813 --> 24:59.931
so you're gonna you'd need
about two more guys

24:59.932 --> 25:01.683
to make it a fair fight,
you fricking loser.

25:01.684 --> 25:02.901
Oh, I'm a loser?

25:02.902 --> 25:04.569
Did I tell you I got
into Ohio State?

25:04.570 --> 25:05.987
Yeah, I'm gonna
play hockey there.

25:05.988 --> 25:08.055
What's your plan
after graduation?

25:08.056 --> 25:11.225
Oh, that's right,
you aren't graduating.

25:11.226 --> 25:13.027
Face it, Puck,
you're the guy

25:13.028 --> 25:15.613
we all used to make fun
of when we were freshman.

25:15.614 --> 25:17.165
The one who used to hang out
hung out in front of the 7-11

25:17.166 --> 25:18.583
picking up on high school girls
after graduating.

25:18.584 --> 25:20.285
In two months you'll
be buying

25:20.286 --> 25:22.287
my little brother beer
and just begging him

25:22.288 --> 25:24.923
to take you to a party.
You're a Lima loser.

25:24.924 --> 25:27.008
I'm going to rip that mullet off
your head.

25:27.009 --> 25:29.460
You want to fight, fine.
But not here.

25:29.461 --> 25:30.678
Out by your Dumpster.

25:30.679 --> 25:32.797
See, I don't want
to get in trouble.

25:32.798 --> 25:34.766
'Cause unlike you,
I got a lot to lose.

25:42.792 --> 25:44.492
How's the wedding
planning going?

25:44.493 --> 25:47.429
Kind of slow lately, but we
still have the same plan:

25:47.430 --> 25:49.631
win Nationals, come back,
graduate, and then

25:49.632 --> 25:51.833
just have a nice little church
wedding performed

25:51.834 --> 25:53.835
by a rabbi with our
nearest and dearest.

25:53.836 --> 25:56.722
And hopefully nobody will get
tragically injured this time.

25:56.723 --> 25:59.174
You think we're gonna win
Nationals?

25:59.175 --> 26:01.810
You know, our first Regionals
and last year,

26:01.811 --> 26:03.979
I had this feeling, like
we were just gonna win.

26:03.980 --> 26:05.513
But this year, nothing.

26:05.514 --> 26:07.866
I just really, really,
want to win, though.

26:07.867 --> 26:09.818
If not for us,
then for Mr. Schue.

26:11.204 --> 26:15.073
What if we go all this way,
and Carmen just says no?

26:15.074 --> 26:16.358
She won't.
She might.

26:16.359 --> 26:18.293
I don't have a back up plan,
all right?

26:18.294 --> 26:20.045
And I don't want to waste
lose a year

26:20.046 --> 26:21.213
of my ingenue eligibility.

26:21.214 --> 26:22.497
You always make it
so hard,

26:22.498 --> 26:24.333
but you were born under
a blessed gold star.

26:24.334 --> 26:25.634
Everyone knows it.

26:25.635 --> 26:27.803
I don't know if I think
that way anymore.

26:27.804 --> 26:30.305
I mean, think of most
of the adults we know, okay?

26:30.306 --> 26:33.058
I bet you that things used to
go their way all the time,

26:33.059 --> 26:34.559
and then one day,
just, they didn't.

26:34.560 --> 26:36.211
And now they
have a job they hate

26:36.212 --> 26:38.313
and they live a life that
they don't even recognize.

26:38.314 --> 26:40.933
And I bet you that they don't
even bother to dream anymore.

26:40.934 --> 26:41.934
That's not everyone.

26:41.935 --> 26:43.185
Yeah, but most people.

26:46.906 --> 26:50.325
No. Okay. I'm not going
there yet.

26:50.326 --> 26:52.560
Carmen is going to say yes.

26:52.561 --> 26:54.613
There's the Rachel Berry
we all know and love.

26:56.449 --> 26:58.233
Yeah, I'm really glad
we're doing this together.

26:58.234 --> 27:00.168
Thank you.

27:00.169 --> 27:01.703
Can you do me one favor?

27:01.704 --> 27:04.589
Before you graduate,
can we sing together?

27:04.590 --> 27:07.843
I would love that.

27:07.844 --> 27:10.012
♪ She's a mania, maniac... ♪

27:13.349 --> 27:15.717
Last chance to walk away

27:15.718 --> 27:17.252
with whatever teeth
you have left, Stickhead.

27:17.253 --> 27:19.521
Please. I just hope you brought
a change of clothes

27:19.522 --> 27:20.722
'cause you're going
Dumpster diving.

27:20.723 --> 27:22.424
But hey, maybe while
you're in there,

27:22.425 --> 27:23.892
you'll find your garbage father.

27:23.893 --> 27:26.094
How's he doing,
by the way?

27:26.095 --> 27:28.196
You know, I tried his microbrew.
It sucked.

27:29.399 --> 27:31.817
Ooh-hoo-hoo-hoo!

27:31.818 --> 27:33.035
Game on.

27:37.740 --> 27:38.606
Oh!

27:40.960 --> 27:43.328
Hit him! Hit him! Hit him!
Take him down!

27:46.966 --> 27:47.782
Hit him!

27:50.003 --> 27:52.804
Hit him!

27:52.805 --> 27:55.307
Hit him! Hit him!

28:02.899 --> 28:05.350
Let's just make this easy.
Hop in there yourself.

28:05.351 --> 28:06.468
Come on, man!

28:17.780 --> 28:21.116
The reign
of Noah Puckerman is over!

28:21.117 --> 28:25.420
Your winner,
and still a loser.

28:25.421 --> 28:30.926
Loser! Loser!
Loser! Loser! Loser! Loser!

28:30.927 --> 28:32.594
Ah, you want some more,
there, Nancy?

28:35.548 --> 28:37.349
Whoa! Whoa, dude.
What the hell you doing, man?

28:37.350 --> 28:38.717
I'm not a loser!

28:38.718 --> 28:40.969
Drop it!
Get over here!

28:40.970 --> 28:41.836
Drop it!

28:44.390 --> 28:47.192
The show's over!
Everybody go home!

28:47.193 --> 28:49.844
Get out of here!

28:51.364 --> 28:52.647
Except for you.

28:52.648 --> 28:54.282
Come on!

28:56.486 --> 28:58.370
A knife?!

28:58.371 --> 29:00.572
It's rubber. It's just a prop
from <i>West Side Story.</i>

29:00.573 --> 29:01.873
What the hell are you thinking?!

29:01.874 --> 29:03.325
You could get expelled for this!

29:03.326 --> 29:04.626
It doesn't matter.
I'm flunking out!

29:04.627 --> 29:05.860
You've got a record!

29:05.861 --> 29:07.329
You could get
arrested for assault!

29:07.330 --> 29:08.530
I don't care!

29:08.531 --> 29:10.048
Well, you damn well should care!

29:10.049 --> 29:11.416
I'm nothing!

29:13.052 --> 29:15.087
Don't you get it?!
I'm nothing!

29:15.088 --> 29:17.806
I'm the school joke!
A failure!

29:19.592 --> 29:21.643
You don't know what it's like
to be worthless,

29:21.644 --> 29:23.178
where nothing you do matters!

29:23.179 --> 29:25.931
I feel that way every day
of my life!

29:25.932 --> 29:27.715
Every damn day!

29:27.716 --> 29:30.352
You know how many
football games or concerts

29:30.353 --> 29:33.522
my mom's been to in the last four years?
None. Not one.

29:33.523 --> 29:36.274
My dad's been AWOL since
I was ten years old,

29:36.275 --> 29:39.611
which is fine because all he ever
did was tell me I was garbage!

29:39.612 --> 29:41.446
And he must be really
proud of himself

29:41.447 --> 29:42.897
'cause that's exactly
how I turned out!

29:47.403 --> 29:49.037
I'm sorry.

29:49.038 --> 29:51.289
I'm sorry.

29:51.290 --> 29:53.241
Come here.

29:53.242 --> 29:56.595
I'm sorry!

29:56.596 --> 30:00.465
You know, you and me,
we're badasses.

30:00.466 --> 30:04.970
Nobody thinks
anything hurts us, but it does.

30:04.971 --> 30:07.088
It does. It's okay.

30:14.205 --> 30:17.704
♪ But I'm always true to you,
darlin', ♪

30:17.705 --> 30:21.975
♪ In my fashion ♪

30:21.976 --> 30:28.849
♪ Yes, I'm always true
to you... ♪

30:28.850 --> 30:35.355
♪ Darling, in my way... ♪

30:43.782 --> 30:45.565
Breath control is better,

30:45.566 --> 30:47.451
but the phrasing is still
emotionally flaccid.

30:47.452 --> 30:49.169
Emotionally flaccid.

30:49.170 --> 30:50.287
Thank you, Madame Tibideaux.

30:51.289 --> 30:52.184
Thank you.

30:53.758 --> 30:55.909
Madame Tibideaux, hello.
I'm sorry to interrupt,

30:55.910 --> 30:57.127
but it's me, Rachel Berry.

30:58.129 --> 30:59.763
I'm sorry.
I realize that I've

30:59.764 --> 31:01.381
been a little persistent,
but I'm just...

31:01.382 --> 31:05.614
I am a very busy woman.

31:06.721 --> 31:08.421
Every moment I spend deleting

31:08.422 --> 31:10.307
yet another one of your
voicemails

31:10.308 --> 31:12.309
about lost hopes and dreams

31:12.310 --> 31:14.311
takes time away
from another student.

31:14.312 --> 31:17.030
What makes you think you
are entitled

31:17.031 --> 31:20.433
to any more attention than
other hundreds of people I see

31:20.434 --> 31:21.935
with the same hopes
and dreams?

31:21.936 --> 31:24.437
No. I'm so sorry. I don't mean
to take time away from them.

31:24.438 --> 31:26.240
But you do.

31:26.241 --> 31:27.774
And I'm tired of it.

31:27.775 --> 31:29.827
Ms. Tibideaux, I know
exactly how you feel.

31:29.828 --> 31:31.712
Rachel Berry is
a pain in the ass.

31:31.713 --> 31:34.047
What she wants, she gets.

31:34.048 --> 31:36.783
And I've spent a lot of time
resenting her for it.

31:36.784 --> 31:39.953
But the fact is, she gets
it because she's exceptional.

31:39.954 --> 31:41.839
Not just the voice,
which is sick,

31:41.840 --> 31:44.091
but the focus, the drive.

31:44.092 --> 31:46.310
How often do you come across
the real deal?

31:46.311 --> 31:48.846
The "real deal" that couldn't
remember the words to the song?

31:48.847 --> 31:51.298
Which was as rare as a Bigfoot sighting.
She had an off day,

31:51.299 --> 31:52.599
and that decides
her entire future?

31:52.600 --> 31:54.768
Ms. Tibideaux, I realize
that I'm asking you

31:54.769 --> 31:56.803
to take me into special
consideration.

31:56.804 --> 31:59.323
but let me ask you.
You've had an amazing career,

31:59.324 --> 32:01.158
did you get there
by playing by it safe?

32:03.995 --> 32:06.613
Please, we're performing
our Nationals in Chicago,

32:06.614 --> 32:08.615
and we saw that you're gonna
be singing there

32:08.616 --> 32:10.000
at the Lyric Opera.

32:10.001 --> 32:12.152
And before you close the door,
I just,

32:12.153 --> 32:14.922
I need you to hear me sing.
I have to.

32:14.923 --> 32:17.457
There's nothing that
I'm as good at

32:17.458 --> 32:21.011
or as passionate about or that
brings me that much joy.

32:21.012 --> 32:22.930
And I think that
that sets me apart.

32:26.134 --> 32:29.269
And I think it's time for you
and your friend to go.

32:31.522 --> 32:34.308
Okay, but I just want you
to know that...

32:34.309 --> 32:36.676
I'll see you again next year.

32:36.677 --> 32:38.695
And every year after
that until I get in.

32:38.696 --> 32:41.398
Didn't I read somewhere
that you

32:41.399 --> 32:42.983
auditioned for Juilliard
four times?

32:46.854 --> 32:48.455
Thank you.

33:00.385 --> 33:01.885
Hey, baby.

33:01.886 --> 33:03.387
I got us a couple of pies.

33:03.388 --> 33:05.305
Hawaiian, your favorite.

33:08.209 --> 33:10.894
I'm sorry, Shannon.

33:10.895 --> 33:12.963
You know how sorry I am.

33:12.964 --> 33:15.766
Listen, guy
from Michigan

33:15.767 --> 33:18.551
has been poaching every
kid I took a sniff of

33:18.552 --> 33:20.654
and everyone's on my ass

33:20.655 --> 33:23.824
and, if I'm being
totally honest...

33:25.994 --> 33:28.829
I'm always feeling like
I'm disappointing you.

33:30.531 --> 33:34.734
And... it doesn't matter.

33:34.735 --> 33:36.336
You know why?

33:36.337 --> 33:39.373
'Cause I know I can't
lose my cool anymore,

33:39.374 --> 33:41.091
and I won't.

33:41.092 --> 33:42.476
I promise.

33:44.929 --> 33:47.014
Oh, come on, baby, sit
down. We're celebrating.

33:47.015 --> 33:50.050
You remember that, uh, that
bear of a lineman I told you

33:50.051 --> 33:51.885
I was hot on from
Newton South?

33:51.886 --> 33:53.937
Got him to sign on
the dotted line!

33:57.191 --> 33:58.976
Come on, baby.

34:01.429 --> 34:02.763
You got my word.

34:12.040 --> 34:15.625
What, are you gonna stab me?

34:15.626 --> 34:16.775
Not with that one.

34:16.777 --> 34:18.128
It's fake.

34:18.129 --> 34:19.963
Maybe the big one
in the kitchen.

34:19.964 --> 34:23.783
The one I've been sleeping
with at night under my pillow.

34:23.784 --> 34:26.453
Oh, God.

34:26.454 --> 34:28.422
Baby, I'm so sorry.

34:30.391 --> 34:32.559
I mean, how did we let it
get so out of hand?

34:32.560 --> 34:33.527
I'm out.

34:35.596 --> 34:37.848
I got shame about what
happened between us,

34:37.849 --> 34:41.268
but I leave that here
with my ring and with you.

34:41.268 --> 34:43.853
Oh, please, please.

34:43.855 --> 34:47.190
Don't... don't leave me, okay?

34:47.190 --> 34:51.110
You can't hate me anymore
than I already hate myself.

34:51.112 --> 34:52.779
I don't hate you!

34:52.780 --> 34:54.447
That's the awful part of it.

34:54.449 --> 34:55.831
I love you!

34:55.833 --> 34:59.453
But what does that say
about what I think of me?

35:03.257 --> 35:06.343
What are you gonna do, huh,
just walk out on me?

35:06.344 --> 35:09.346
Who's going to love you
the way I loved you, Shannon?

35:09.347 --> 35:11.798
Who's going to love you now?

35:13.935 --> 35:15.802
Me.

35:25.012 --> 35:29.316
♪ You, with your words like
knives and swords and weapons ♪

35:29.317 --> 35:31.017
♪ That you use against me ♪

35:31.018 --> 35:35.122
♪ You have knocked me
off my feet again ♪

35:35.123 --> 35:36.856
♪ Got me feeling
like I'm nothing ♪

35:36.857 --> 35:40.710
♪ You, with your voice
like nails on a chalkboard ♪

35:40.711 --> 35:42.412
♪ Calling me out
when I'm wounded ♪

35:42.413 --> 35:46.299
♪ You, pickin'
on the weaker man ♪

35:49.554 --> 35:55.892
♪ Well, you can take me down
with just one single blow ♪

35:55.893 --> 36:00.313
♪ But you don't know
what you don't know ♪

36:00.314 --> 36:05.902
♪ Someday I'll be living
in a big old city ♪

36:05.903 --> 36:09.940
♪ And all you're ever
gonna be is mean ♪

36:11.826 --> 36:17.614
♪ Someday I'll be big enough
so you can't hit me ♪

36:17.615 --> 36:21.451
♪ And all you're ever gonna be
is mean ♪

36:21.452 --> 36:25.755
♪ Why you gotta be so mean? ♪

36:25.756 --> 36:29.543
♪ And I can see you
years from now in a bar ♪

36:29.544 --> 36:32.746
♪ Talking over a football game ♪

36:32.747 --> 36:35.248
♪ With that same
big, loud opinion ♪

36:35.249 --> 36:38.385
♪ But nobody's listening ♪

36:38.386 --> 36:46.893
♪ Washed up and ranting about
the same old bitter things ♪

36:46.894 --> 36:53.316
♪ Drunk and grumbling on
about how I can't sing ♪

36:53.317 --> 36:55.702
♪ But all you are is mean ♪

36:58.656 --> 37:00.740
♪ All you are is mean ♪

37:00.741 --> 37:02.775
♪ And a liar ♪

37:02.776 --> 37:03.994
♪ And pathetic ♪

37:03.995 --> 37:06.463
♪ And alone in life and mean ♪

37:06.464 --> 37:10.950
♪ And mean, and mean, and mean ♪

37:10.951 --> 37:17.674
♪ But someday I'll be living
in a big old city ♪

37:17.675 --> 37:21.678
♪ And all you're ever gonna be
is mean ♪

37:21.679 --> 37:23.730
♪ Yeah ♪

37:23.731 --> 37:27.984
♪ Someday I'll be living
in a big old city ♪

37:27.985 --> 37:29.819
♪ Why gotta be so mean? ♪

37:29.820 --> 37:33.940
♪ And you're ever gonna be
is mean ♪

37:33.941 --> 37:37.577
♪ Why you gotta be so mean? ♪

37:39.697 --> 37:42.949
So why are you in here singing
all by your lonesome?

37:42.950 --> 37:45.418
Just trying out a song
for Nationals.

37:45.419 --> 37:47.120
I gotta win at something.

37:47.121 --> 37:49.506
Well, you may not know it,
but you already have.

37:49.507 --> 37:51.424
I talked to
Mrs. Doosenberry.

37:51.425 --> 37:54.294
She's gonna let you have
another go at that test.

37:54.295 --> 37:56.179
Why? She hates me.

37:56.180 --> 37:57.830
Hated your attitude.

37:57.831 --> 37:59.666
But I told her
how you wiggled

37:59.667 --> 38:02.001
into a skirt for the
good of your team.

38:02.002 --> 38:03.503
She's into that?

38:03.504 --> 38:04.804
Oh, should've known
Doosenberry was a lady-lover

38:04.805 --> 38:06.673
when she didn't climb
aboard the Puck wagon.

38:06.674 --> 38:10.360
No, when you did that, you showed
that you cared about something.

38:10.361 --> 38:14.013
Something way bigger
than just you.

38:14.014 --> 38:15.982
That's all she ever
wanted from you.

38:15.983 --> 38:18.451
That's all any of us
teachers ever wanted.

38:18.452 --> 38:21.488
So, you're gonna
retake the exam

38:21.489 --> 38:23.990
next week, and I'm gonna
help you through it.

38:23.991 --> 38:26.693
Why would you do that,
help me like that?

38:26.694 --> 38:31.248
Because, Noah, you will never
know how much you've helped me.

38:32.633 --> 38:34.251
You are loved, punkin.

38:34.252 --> 38:36.369
You are not alone.

38:44.475 --> 38:45.642
Aah, I pricked my thumb!

38:45.643 --> 38:47.477
Okay, Costume Committee?

38:47.478 --> 38:48.845
Sucks.

38:48.846 --> 38:50.096
Why do we have
to do all the work?

38:50.097 --> 38:51.481
Quinn says
it's because we're the newbies,

38:51.482 --> 38:53.182
- and we gotta pay our dues.
- Whatever.

38:53.183 --> 38:56.069
It's ridick the seniors treat us
like plebes.

38:56.070 --> 38:57.987
I mean, this is Rachel
Berry's dress, right?

38:57.988 --> 38:59.639
She should sew it herself.

38:59.640 --> 39:02.475
Rachel is probably practicing
her songs right now,

39:02.476 --> 39:03.809
over and over again,

39:03.810 --> 39:05.612
until her vocal chords bleed.

39:05.613 --> 39:07.614
And none of us would
be going to Chicago

39:07.615 --> 39:09.549
if not for her commitment
to Glee Club,

39:09.550 --> 39:11.000
so show some respect.

39:11.001 --> 39:12.952
While we're acting like
shrubbery in the background?

39:12.953 --> 39:15.455
Put in the work...

39:15.456 --> 39:17.123
be a good team player,

39:17.124 --> 39:18.824
and you'll get your solos.

39:18.825 --> 39:20.293
And maybe next year
it'll be

39:20.294 --> 39:22.795
as part of a group
that won Nationals.

39:22.796 --> 39:24.830
And this costume
is yours, Sugar,

39:24.831 --> 39:26.799
but I'm happy
to be sewing it.

39:26.800 --> 39:29.018
Because the truth is,

39:29.019 --> 39:32.722
it takes a lot of crystals
to make something shine.

39:39.563 --> 39:42.231
Now, that's great, and then
we shift to the Trouble Tones

39:42.232 --> 39:44.150
for Gaga's "Edge of Glory,"
which is up-tempo.

39:44.151 --> 39:46.786
I like this.
This will work.

39:46.787 --> 39:49.739
William, I can taste
your Axe Body Spray.

39:50.958 --> 39:51.958
Hey, you.

39:51.959 --> 39:54.577
Going somewhere, Shannon?

39:54.578 --> 39:56.913
I'd like to be a chaperone
for Nationals.

39:56.914 --> 39:59.165
I'll pay my own way
and I'll sleep on the bus.

39:59.166 --> 40:01.367
You don't have to
